HEADWORD: Upkeep
<hw>Up"keep`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of keeping up, or maintaining; maintenance of persons, organizations, or
objects such as machinery, by providing a location, repairs, and
consumable items when necessary.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Horse artillery . . .
expensive in the <xex>upkeep</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Scribner's
Mag.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Small outlays for repairs or <qex>upkeep</qex> of buildings.</q>
<rj><qau>A. R. Colquhoun.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the cost of providing upkeep{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upland</ent>⟦br⟧
